### Project Management
* Software Lifecycle Phases
    * Requirements
    * Design
    * Code
    * Test


### Requirements Phase
* Be clear about the primary goal
* Identify key priorities - Time, Money, Function
* Use past history to set budget
* Top 10 design objectives
* Weekly customer interactions
* Who is responsible for the content?


### Design
* Design for usability
* Map of pages and navigation
* Sketch page layout as a wire-frame
* Gather, create, and organize text, image, and video content 
* Visual appearance
* Special controls and page design
* Task break down


### Code
* Code each milestone one at a time
* Plan to reuse as much code as possible
* Learning plan
* Update the schedule to match reality
* Every file that must be under version control
* Simplify the design repeatedly


### Test
* Weekly customer meetings
* Acceptance criteria
* Issue tracking (fix every defect)
* Code and design reviews
* Release criteria
* Usability testing
* Customer sign-off


